version.description:
Unicode 1.1 were pre-dated emoji inclusion in Unicode by 17 years, and included many characters primarily sourced from the Zapf Dingbats font.

The following characters were added to Unicode in 1993 and many were given emoji presentation status in the years 2010-2015.

emoji_net_data.definition: An arrow pointing diagonally in an up-left, or north-west direction. Up-left Arrow was approved as part of Unicode 1.1 in 1993 under the nam http://emojipedia.org/north-west-arrow/
emoji_net_data.name: up-left arrow

bn:13612752a: Between the cardinal directions, as for example southwest between south and west.

bn:00113407a: Extending or moving toward a higher place
Moving up, directed toward a higher place.

bn:00005896n: A mark to indicate a direction or relation
A mark to indicate a direction or relation.
A sign or symbol used to indicate a direction (e.g. \to).

bn:00058102n: The four cardinal directions or cardinal points are the directions of north, east, south, and west, commonly denoted by their initials: N, E, S, W. East and west are at right angles to north and south, with east being in the clockwise direction of rotation from north and west being directly opposite east.
Any of the four principal compass directions - north, south, east and west
The direction corresponding to the northwestward compass point
